cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the integration of heterogeneous vocabularies and ontologies, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of WordNet as a semantic hub also falls under these categories. The paper also involves unsupervised mapping techniques (cs.IR) and evaluation of the approach (cs.DB). Finally, the paper deals with the semantic aspects of geographic information, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
